As a new member, it is important to remember that finding a guide or mentor within your skill-set can be extremely beneficial for your professional development. A guide can help you navigate the workings of the company and point out potential next steps in your journey here.

We encourage you to consider finding a mentor who has a skill set that matches the areas you are interested in developing, and who has a personality that you respect and can learn from. Unlike a guide they can also provide valuable advice and support for personal development and business ideas. A mentor can be a valuable resource and can help you make the most of your time at [Tech Enterprise].

If you have any questions or need assistance finding a mentor, please don't hesitate to reach out to an Officer or Guide. We are here to support you in any way we can.

